"script": "If you boiled away every ocean and scraped up all the salt left behind, you'd have enough to bury every continent under a layer 500 feet thick. That's a wall of salt taller than a 40-story skyscraper, blanketing all the land on Earth. You see, the oceans hold about 50 quadrillion tons of dissolved salt. And if you spread it evenly across the whole planet, including the seafloor, it would still pile up 150 feet high. So the sea isn't just water, it's hiding a buried mountain of salt that could swallow every city we've ever built.",
